post_text:
Dear Itineris Parents,

The Board of Trustees will review Itineris' proposed fee policy, schedule, and spend plan for school year 2020-21, as well as receive public comment, during their regularly scheduled board meeting at 7:30 am this Friday, February 28th.

You are invited to provide public comment at the meeting or via this form: https://forms.gle/gcEFaSKPMmmce4QR8 (Google sign-in required). Should you choose to attend in person, public comment will be limited to 3 minutes per person and the board will not respond to or make decisions regarding the fees during these meetings. The board will vote on the proposed plans at the March meeting.

Thank you for your support.

post_text:
Happy Wednesday Students!!

Unfortunately our oven has a gas connection issue and for safety reasons, we had to shut it down. A repair person is scheduled but they won't be here in time to cook today's lunches.

SO.... if you ordered lunch or want to eat lunch, we are serving turkey sandwiches, PB jammers, and a few grab and go items. We will have enough for those that want to eat but the main dishes will not be served.

The staff was able to cook pre-ordered breakfast items so feel free to get your order from them as usual.

We apologize for the inconvenience and will get the oven working ASAP.

post_text:
Flu season is upon us and this year is particularly problematic do to the severity of the flu strands. We have had several confirmed cases of both Influenza A and B and even though those students are staying at home, exposure may have been pre-symptomatic. If your student is experiencing flu-like symptoms, please have them stay at home to alleviate the spread of the flu. Students can work with their teachers to get missing assignments.

Students, please wash your hands before eating or touching your face to avoid exposure especially when touching public surfaces such as doors and desks. Thank you!

post_text: Itineris Early College High School (located in West Jordan) is a 10th-12th grade charter school that blends a small, STEM school environment with the opportunity for students to earn up to two years of college credit. Partnered with Salt Lake Community College, Itineris is a school where expectations are high, but students are given a lot of support to achieve their goals and reach their potential. Relationships and personal connections between and among students, faculty, and home/community matter. Apply today! post_text: Itineris Early College High School is a 10th-12th grade charter school that blends a small, STEM school environment with the opportunity for students to earn up to two years college credit. Consistently recognized as one of the best high schools in Utah, Itineris focuses on using technology to help students achieve their potential. Relationships matter, as building strong student to teacher relationships are essential to hands-on learning. It’s a journey of a lifetime. Wanna learn more? Come join us at a Family Information Night! Upcoming Family Info Night Dates: December 5, 2019 @ 6:00pm, January 8, 2020 @ 6:00pm, January 22, 2020 @ 6:00pm, February 6, 2020 @ 6:00pm. Or visit us at iechs.org. *Images are not created by us. Revised by @iechs

post_text:
Read below-great tips for college success! Best wishes to our recent grads that are headed out to college soon! Posted @withrepost • @suutbirds Transitioning from high school to college can be challenging for students, but we are here to share a few tips to make it easier! 📚
1. Don't be afraid to form study groups, it is much easier to get through tough courses when you have peer help.
2. Get out and meet people! Networking in college can be extremely useful to you post-graduation.
3. Take advantage of open spots in your schedule and use it to study. Don't fall behind and end up cramming the entire day before a big test!
4. Remember that your happiness is up to you. Surround yourself with people that make you feel good and try new things!
5. Stay in touch. Don't forget about your family and friends back home!

#TBirdNation, add to our list below to help new freshmen transition into college life!

What did you love about Itineris? Why would you recommend it to others? Here's a link to the page: http://www.iechs.org/apps/memoirs/

Also, if you haven't seen our new alumni directory yet, you should check it out and register: http://www.iechs.org/apps/directory/

post_text: Construction update: Everything is on schedule and looking good! The building is now less than 7 weeks away from completion.
text: Construction update: Everything is on schedule and looking good! The building is now less than 7 weeks away from completion.

post_text: We just said goodbye to this building for the last time! We are officially moved out! Our phone number is not moving with us, so we will be sure to let you know when we have a new phone number. In the meantime, please contact us via email. A list of staff members working over the summer and their contact information can be found here: http://bit.ly/TkaYAH

post_text: Today was a big day! If you thought moving a house was hard, try moving a school! We filled 3 full-sized semi trailers today (packed very tightly, floor to ceiling) and we still aren't done! Thank you to all those who helped out!
